===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|rifler||to scrape off, plunder|lang=fro}}, from [[Old Low Franconian]] *''riffilōn'' (compare obsolete {{etyl|nl|-}} ''rijffelen'' 'to scrape', {{etyl|ang}} {{term|geriflian||to wrinkle|lang=ang}}, {{etyl|gmh}} {{term|riffeln||to scratch, heckle (flax)|lang=gmh}}, {{etyl|goh}} {{term|riffilōn||to saw, rub apart|lang=goh}}), frequentative of {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|rīfanan|lang=gem-pro}} (compare {{etyl|non}} {{term|rifa||to tear, break|lang=non}}). More at {{term|rive}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈraɪfəl/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/"raIf@l/}}
* {{audio|en-us-rifle.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

